        <summary>Calculate horizontal gradient magnitude for edge enhancement and structural mapping</summary>
        <usage>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;"&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The total horizontal gradient (THG) is calculated as sqrt(dx² + dy²) where dx and dy are horizontal derivatives. This transformation enhances linear features and geological contacts.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Applications:&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;• Delineating geological contacts and fault systems&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;• Enhancing linear magnetic anomalies&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;• Structural interpretation and mapping&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Results are always positive and provide excellent edge enhancement.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</usage>
